C:\Users\yann.yu>virtualenv --version
15.0.3

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

(1) install virtualenvwrapper in home dir:
pip install virtualenvwrapper-win

(2) tell bash about it
In Windows, the default path for WORKON_HOME is %USERPROFILE%Envs

add to the bottom:

# Virtualenvwrapper settings
In Windows, the default path for WORKON_HOME is %USERPROFILE%Envs

(3) 
mkvirtualenv -p C:\Users\yann.yu\AppData\Local\Continuum\Anaconda3\python dabeaz
mkvirtualenv dabeaz

(4) toggle:
deactivate
workon dabeaz



++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

rmvirtualenv dabeaz

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Other useful commands
lsvirtualenv
List all of the environments.
cdvirtualenv
Navigate into the directory of the currently activated virtual environment, so you can browse its site-packages, for example.
cdsitepackages
Like the above, but directly into site-packages directory.
lssitepackages
Shows contents of site-packages directory.
